# No Cursor Attribution

Never add Cursor, Claude, or any AI tool attribution to commits, code comments, or PR descriptions.

## Forbidden

- `Co-authored-by:` trailers referencing Cursor, Claude, GPT, or any AI assistant
- "Generated by Cursor", "AI-generated", "Created with Claude", etc. in code comments
- "🤖 Generated with..." footers in commit messages or PR bodies
- Sign-offs that mention AI tools

## Examples

```
❌ BAD commit message:
feat: add login flow

Co-authored-by: Cursor <noreply@cursor.com>
🤖 Generated with Cursor

✅ GOOD commit message:
feat: add login flow
```

```ts
// ❌ BAD
// Generated by Cursor
function handler() { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
function handler() { ... }
```

## Why

Authorship and code comments should reflect the human author and the intent of the change. Tool attribution clutters git history, code, and PR descriptions without adding long-term value.
